## When the Plan Meets Reality

Day 80 built the audit readiness framework — the evidence trail, the people preparation, the narrative consistency check, and the IR-3 tabletop exercise design question that ended the entry: a scenario where the primary contact is unreachable and the IRP does not explicitly address the escalation path. That open question is where Day 81 begins.

The OpenMRS Incident Response Plan exists. The HIPAA breach notification workflow was added in Q1 monitoring (POA&M item 006 closed). The technical incident response capability — GuardDuty detection, Security Hub aggregation, CloudTrail forensic evidence — was verified during the formal assessment. What has not been tested is whether the people who would execute the IRP can actually execute it under pressure, with incomplete information, at 2am, when things are not going according to the procedure document.

Day 81 examines incident response and business continuity planning at the operational depth that the project has established for everything else — not as abstract concepts, but as specific decisions and procedures for the OpenMRS system, with honest attention to where the current program is strong and where it has gaps that testing will surface.

